license: OFL
category: sans-serif
subsets: menu,latin

family: Nobile

designer: Vernon Adams

approved: true
description: <p>&quot;Nobile&quot; \
  is designed to work with the technologies of digital screens and \
  handheld devices without losing the distinctive look more usually found \
  in fonts designed for printing. Going back to William Morris's baseline \
  &quot;Have nothing in your house that you do not know to be useful, or \
  believe to be beautiful&quot;, the aim was to design a font that could \
  function well, have good legibility on screen yet also be good looking, \
  not only at larger display sizes but also right down to small text \
  sizes.</p>

font.Nobile-Regular.ttf.style: normal
font.Nobile-Medium.ttf.style: normal
font.Nobile-Bold.ttf.style: normal

font.Nobile-Italic.ttf.style: italic
font.Nobile-MediumItalic.ttf.style: italic
font.Nobile-BoldItalic.ttf.style: italic

font.Nobile-Regular.ttf.weight: 400
font.Nobile-Medium.ttf.weight: 500
font.Nobile-Bold.ttf.weight: 700

font.Nobile-Italic.ttf.weight: 400
font.Nobile-MediumItalic.ttf.weight: 500
font.Nobile-BoldItalic.ttf.weight: 700

